the mark thomas comedy product  wikipedia the mark thomas comedy product from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search the mark thomas comedy product starring mark thomas country of origin united kingdom original languages english no of series  no of episodes  production producers geoff atkinson running time  minutes production companys vera productions ltd release original network channel  original release  february  –  october  the mark thomas comedy product was a television show fronted by the english comedian presenter political activist and reporter mark thomas it was broadcast in the uk on channel  from  february  to  october  the show described as a brilliantly ludicrous alternative to watchdog was a hybrid of comedy and serious politics with thomas often using silly or surreal methods to gain interviews with politicians and corporations and to highlight issues episode guideedit series episode title synopsis   bear necessities interviews several mps dressed as a bear mtv presenter bumrush of livetvs news bunny jerry hayes dresses up as a blokes knob  mcdonalds and mad saddam mcfun at mcdonalds in which thomas purchases  p burgers then sets a burger van up outside to resell them then turns up in a clown car with clowns then a tank and eventually a lorry with a rock band on the back and gets banned also features ecgd bad debts in iraq and nigeria  parliament mark stands for parliament at harmsworth gives malcolm rifkind some fashion tips  tours of london conditionally exempt art phones tory party central office and upsets them  mi and birching young offenders mark visits mi phones the columbian embassy loses a few footballs and videos the video voyeur  show in a flat mark bets the production budget for the last show on a horse in the  from doncaster loses and has to make the last show of series one in his mates living room tries to give cash away at the bank of england and raises money at the torython series episode title synopsis   campbell fayed and straw cannabis surgery with jack straw alistair campbells porn past mohammed al fayed draws his own todger  church money mark probes the ethics of the church of englands investments and runs a float at the lord mayors show  sellafield and mice the friendly face of genetic engineering duponts onco mouse radioactive pigeon guano at sellafield burston marsteller and mark does his impression of lord simon  virgin trains mark runs a promotion on the concourse relabels a few virgin trains and gets a song played on virgin radio  lottery  cewa and dome mark investigates the governments new deal delivers pizzas and discusses abortion with the prolifers here and abroad  number stations more conditionally exempt art santa goes to the dome and mark reveals what the series  backdrops are all about series episode title synopsis   arms fair mark sets up a pr company at an arms fair in greece and interviews major general widjojo from indonesia after discussing with the major general the armys involvement in the massacre of  innocent civilians in a churchyard i spent the afternoon with an iranian arms dealer talking through whether a mortar bomb could be the solution to moles on my back lawn  indonesian torture mark pitches for pr training for the indonesian army and has a look at the uk arms export industry and what the dti lets it get away with  geoffrey robinson weirder than a goat milkshake  all about geoffrey robinson  local referendums organise your own local referendum pfi the nhs and the air traffic control service  nuclear trains after the residents of cricklewood find out they will be getting nuclear waste in their back yard mark goes to dungeness to guard a train carrying nuclear waste and add a little bit of information to the visitors centre  company directors company directors home addresses strikers and electrician safety on the jubilee line extension  the menwith hill tours mark has a scare whilst hotair ballooning over raf menwith hill a usrun listening station in yorkshire  updates a bit of a rag bag of a show  william hague at loughbough university mark organises a labour conference standing ovation house of lords attendance the nutty john battle updates on nuclear trains the dti and the showgirls of truth  special report asylum and immigration bill series episode title synopsis   burma  premier oil human rights in burma premier oil and robin cook  iraqi sanctions mark tried to take a sanctions busting teddy bear to iraq a beanie baby to the whitehouse and featured a woman with a price on her head for saving lives  nestle nestle and baby milk action   aldermaston awe in this show mark thomas cast his critical allseeing eye on things nuclear and took a peek over the fence at the atomic weapons establishment at aldermaston and unexpectedly became the first programme since the s to be invited to film an interview from within the base  ecgd the export credit guarantee department and their role in arms dealing  david shayler mark met david shayler found out about his own mi file enlisted some acrobatic mailmen came face to face with jack straw investigated the lack of accountability of the intelligence services and the lunacy of the official secrets act  ppl human milk production human milk from cows and more baby milk action  xenotransplantation pigs heart or pigs ear this week mark looked at the wacky world of xenotransplantation and found out how politicians may be playing god  ecgd ilisu dam ecgd spending out of control and the ilisu dam in turkey  government accountability law enforcement under jack straw freedom of information visiting pinochet and the cambridge  imprisoned for  years under section  of the misuse of drugs act  series updates series round up and a day out at the millennium dome series episode title synopsis   cctv  the data protection act the data protection act and the cctv competition  meps interests the register of meps interests and how they are lobbied  michael meacher the uk mps register of interests  pester power in this show mark investigated corporate advertising and arranged a debate about conditions in clothing factories in indonesia between the global affairs director of adidas union activists from jakarta and richard howitt mep in a school where year  students were able to ask questions of the senior adidas representative in charge of global marketing  balfour beatty ecgd revisited and the ilisu dam  tube privatisation ppp and the london underground  series updates series updates and william hagues speaking fees series episode title synopsis   organophosphates illegal pesticides used in uk via legal loophole  drug dumping corporations dumping expired drugs in poor countries for tax breaks  corporate killing corporate killing and the simon jones case  yusufeli dam more dams ilisu and yusefeli balfour beatty and amec  quango state quangos transparency accountability and the select committee  arms dealing how to become an arms dealer in  days specials broadcast date title synopsis  thomas country mark poses as a rightwing farmer who infiltrated genuine farming conferences to investigate the true aims and ambitions of the countryside lobby  mark thomas secret map of britain mark thomas draws up a map of britain that reveals the places the government and the establishment do not want the public to know about disproves the claim that the government is an open institution and looks at the secret democracy that britain really is  mark thomas weapons inspector mark assumes the role of a weapons inspector and attempts to uncover british and american weapons of mass destruction  mark thomas debt collector post war iraq is bust the country owes  to various companies banks and countries from loanscredit which it took to build palaces buy weapons and such mark thomas decides to try to help out by taking it onto himself to try to raise money to help them out referencesedit  upton sam preview the mark thomas comedy product select emap metro march    external links