ns become reality in april  thomas was awarded £ compensation for a search carried out by police in  he had been unlawfully subject to a stopandsearch without adequate cause after speaking at an antiarms rally during  thomas decided to go rambling in the middle east and walked the entire length of the israeli separation barrier crossing between the israeli and the palestinian side his touring show entitled walking the wall  was shortlisted for the amnesty international freedom of expression award and his book extreme rambling recounted the story thomas revealed in  that he had discovered through a data protection request that he had been under police surveillance as a result of his investigative journalism for channel  and the new statesman and put on the domestic extremist database he cautioned other journalists i apologise for the boastful tone but the police have monitored public interest investigations in my case since  more importantly if the police are keeping tabs on a lightweight like myself then they are doing the same and more to others this is more than supposition as i know of other nuj members on the database the following year thomas and five journalists and photographers who had also been under surveillance by the london metropolitan police services national domestic extremism and disorder intelligence unit ndediu began legal action against the force the ndedius reports obtained by thomas described him as a general rabble rouser and alleged comedian and stated mark thomas stops has quantity of cress on rear of his cycle he told the independents adam lusher the polices powers of observation are to be admired i did indeed have cress on my bike but is it really suitable to spend taxpayers money observing the movement of cress televisionedit friday night live channel   saturday zoo channel   viva cabaret channel   denton channel  australia  the mark thomas comedy product later renamed the mark thomas product channel  which ran for six series totalling  episodes – dispatches the lie of the land channel   thomas country channel   the immigration and asylum bill channel   secret map of britain channel   dispatches mark thomas — broom cupboard inspector channel   dispatches mark thomas — debt collector channel   dispatches after school arms club channel   dispatches mark thomas on coca cola channel   radioedit the mary whitehouse experience radio   the mix radio   sleeping with the nme radio   loose talk radio  – booked radio  – celluloid psychiatrists radio   left bank of the mind radio   mark thomas presents… radio   shows on stan freberg the firesign theatre shelley berman and mort sahl chain reaction radio   my life in serious organised crime radio   ramblings radio   walking the ridgeway track in wiltshire and oxfordshire mark thomas the manifesto radio  –present bravo figaro radio   discographyedit sex filth and religion video  live  dambusters  the night war broke out  mark thomas comedy show dvd  mark thomasserious organised criminal dvd  bravo figaro  live toursedit as used on the famous nelson mandela  serious organised criminal  belching out the devil  its the stupid economy extreme rambling – walking the wall  bravo figaro   acts of minor dissent  cuckooed  trespass  the red shed  other live showsedit mark thomas metrix consortium at the open university  september  awardsedit time out comedy award  perrier comedy award nominee  in addition to being recognised for his comedy career mark thomas has been awarded various citations for his political campaigning including kurdish national congress medal of honour  international service award for the global defence of human rights  mediactivist awards   former guinness world record holder for most number of political demonstrations in  hours he was also made an honorary doctor of letters by the university of bradford on  december  in recognition of his peace campaigning and services to comedy politicsedit in his  march  new statesman column mark placed a bounty on the head of us president george bush to the value of £ his total earnings writing for the magazine to that point in february  british entertainers david baddiel bill bailey morwenna banks sanjeev bhaskar jo brand russell brand rob brydon jimmy carr jack dee omid djalili sean lock lee mack alexei sayle meera syal mark thomas said in an open letter printed in the times newspaper of the baháí leaders to be on trial in iran in reality their only “crime” which the current regime finds intolerable is that they hold a religious belief that is different from the majority… we register our solidarity with all those in iran who are being persecuted for promoting the best development of society …and with the governments human rights organisations and people of goodwill throughout the world who have so far raised their voices calling for a fair trial if not the complete release of the baha’i leaders in iran echoing the comments earlier in the month made by two hundred and sixty seven nonbaháí iranian academics writers artists journalists and activists from  countries including iran who signed an open letter of apology posted to iraniancom and stating they were ashamed and pledging their support in baháís achieving the rights detailed in the universal declaration of human rights for the baháís in iran see persecution of baháís prior to the  uk general election he was one of several celebrities who endorsed the parliamentary candidacy of the green partys caroline lucas see alsoedit ilısu dam campaign robert newman southeastern anatolia project corporate crime serious organised crime and police act  see protests near parliament section notesedit  a b c d phil daoust  january  stand up and be taunted the guardian retrieved    biography markthomasinfocom archived from the original on  retrieved    comedian mark thomas my dad was a rightwing thatcher supporter metrocouk  october  retrieved  april    cornock david  october  waleswestminster newslog bbc news online retrieved  may    a b